Scripts Downloaded from Internet
[Internal Justification/Use Case] A file/script was detected and/or blocked by the agent that was downloaded from the internet by the user. This recommendation template is intended to cover cases where the script may not be malicious or was already blocked and resolved via PAAs.  


Unknown Files/Scripts/Commands Template
Customer Recommendation Action:

Bitdefender MDR analysts recommend taking the following actions:

Restrict Script Permissions: Implement strict permission controls on systems, only allowing trusted users to execute scripts. Use group policies or local policies to enforce this on Windows, Mac, and Linux systems.
User Training and Awareness: Educate users on the risks associated with downloading and running scripts from the internet. Conduct regular training on identifying potential malicious scripts, phishing, and safe downloading practices.

 

Customer Recommendation Reason:

The <file> was captured within a detection by the Bitdefender agent. Downloading and running scripts from untrusted sources can expose systems to malware, data breaches, and unauthorized access. Users often lack the expertise to assess whether a script is safe, making them susceptible to social engineering attacks. User training further empowers users to recognize unsafe practices, creating a security-aware culture.

Host(s): <Host(s)>

File Path(s): <File_Path(s)>

