Unmanaged Host Identified
[Internal Justification/Use Case] While working network detections, unmanaged assets can be identified, via IP addresses, as sources of scanning and other activities.


Unmanaged Host Identified
Customer Recommendation Action:

During an investigation, MDR analysts found that the host with IP address "X.X.X.X" does not have the Bitdefender agent installed. MDR analysts recommend installing the agent on this host in order to ensure the host is protected against cybersecurity threats.

Customer Recommendation Reason:

To effectively monitor and protect your systems, it is crucial to have the Bitdefender agent installed on all endpoints in your environment.

 

Reimage Host (Commodity Malware)
[Internal Justification/Use Case] Commodity malware detected on an endpoint where multiple malicious components, persistence mechanisms, or system-level modifications were observed, and targeted remediation cannot reliably ensure system integrity.


Unmanaged Host Identified
Customer Recommendation Action:

Bitdefender MDR analysts recommend reimaging the affected host(s) from a known-good source to ensure complete remediation and restoration of system integrity.

Host(s): <Host(s)>

Customer Recommendation Reason:

The affected host(s) exhibited activity associated with commodity malware, including the presence of multiple malicious components and persistence mechanisms within system locations. Due to the scope of the observed activity and the potential for residual artifacts, full system integrity cannot be reliably assured through targeted cleanup alone. Reimaging provides the most effective method to fully remove malicious artifacts and restore the system to a trusted state.

 

MFA Failed Login Attempt
[Internal Justification/Use Case] We have detections based on user activity from XDR (MFAFailedLoginAttempt). If we do not have PAA, we want to have the customer take the PAA. 


MFA Failed Login Attempt
Customer Recommendation Action:

<Include username and when available the IP that was flagged / For HUN, just include the users if there is a large amount of data>

Reset the following user(s) password: Immediately reset their password, and use a long passphrase for the new password. A passphrase is a string longer than 14 characters formed by a combination of unrelated words. 

<user(s)>

Review MFA Settings: Confirm that the MFA settings are configured correctly, ensuring that the authentication methods are current and accessible.

Authentication Methods: Validate the security and accessibility of your configured authentication methods. These may include mobile apps, SMS, email, or hardware tokens. Regularly review and update your preferred methods to ensure they are the most secure and convenient for your use.

Registered Devices and Phone Numbers: Scrutinize and confirm the devices and phone numbers currently registered for receiving MFA prompts or codes. Any outdated or unrecognized devices and numbers should be promptly removed. Regularly update this information to avoid any discrepancies and ensure the reliability of MFA prompts.

Backup Codes: Reexamine and, if necessary, regenerate your backup codes. Securely store them in an accessible location to ensure availability if the primary MFA method fails or is unavailable. Regularly review the state of your backup codes and update them as required to maintain account security.

 

Customer Recommendation Reason:

The user(s) failed to log in three times consecutively within a short time frame due to invalid MFA.

Scanning Activity
[Internal Justification/Use Case] We have scanning activity within an environment. Either a PAA was/wasn’t taken based on approval. Foundations can’t get a NOT. 


Scanning Activity
Customer Recommendation Action:

Bitdefender MDR analysts recommend taking the following actions to remediate the scanning activity from IP address, <IP>:

Verify the host(s) or network device associated with the IP Address.

Remove the host(s) from the network if it is not authorized to conduct scanning. Whitelist the IP address if the scanning is authorized.

Block the IP/Mac address on applicable network devices if the host(s) cannot be located. 

Add a Bitdefender agent to the host(s), if possible.

Customer Recommendation Reason:

Analysts observed the IP address <IP> conducting scanning activity. Unauthorized scanning is one of the first steps in the attacker methodology that can lead to further exploitation or compromise. 

Endpoint Brute Force Detections
[Internal Justification/Use Case] We have detections based on brute force attacks via EDR/endpoint detections targeting a specific service or host. 


Endpoint Brute Force Detections
Customer Recommendation Action:

Bitdefender MDR analysts have observed inbound brute force attempts targeting the <SERVICE> service on host <HOST>. Analysts recommend to follow the best practices for securing the service against these attacks.

Use strong passwords (long passphrases formed by a combination of unrelated words).

Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA).

Enable account lockout policies.

Limit access to the service by requiring a VPN connection or by whitelisting only approved IP addresses.

Customer Recommendation Reason:

By following these recommendations, you can significantly enhance the security of your <SERVICE> service and reduce the risk of brute force attacks.

