Publicly Accessible Service/System/Application
[Internal Justification/Use Case] We have observed activity/detections for a device that is accessible from the internet. Generally, this will only be relevant as a recommendation in cases where the activity would be considered abnormal (e.g. a user’s device is accessible - not a server hosting a website).  


Publicly Accessible Service/System/Application
Customer Recommendation Action:
Bitdefender MDR analysts recommend ensuring <Service/Application> on <Host> is not directly accessible from the internet or is restricted to only those who need access. 

Customer Recommendation Reason:
Devices that are accessible from the internet will be targeted in scans, brute force attacks, and exploit attempts on any services that accept inbound connections. By restricting access to only necessary parties, the risk of successful cyber attacks can be significantly reduced.

