CAPTCHA Infostealer

Outdated Software/Operating System
Customer Recommendation Action: 

Bitdefender MDR analysts reviewed a detection involving a suspicious PowerShell process initiated by user <user>. on host <hostname>.  Bitdefender MDR analysts recommend taking the following actions:

Reset User Credentials: As a precaution, we recommend resetting credentials for the affected user and enforcing a logout from all active sessions to ensure account integrity.

User Awareness Training: Provide the user with additional training focused on recognizing CAPTCHA-based social engineering tactics and the risks associated with free software downloads, which are often used as lures for malware distribution. Encouraging users to only install software from trusted sources can significantly reduce exposure to these types of threats.

Maintain Browser Hardening: Ensure that ad blockers and enhanced protection features remain enabled in all corporate browsers to minimize risk from malvertising, drive-by downloads, and phishing redirections.

Customer Recommendation Reason:

The observed activity is consistent with an attempted delivery of Infostealer malware, triggered by a malicious CAPTCHA-based social engineering lure. This is an increasingly common technique associated with compromised websites or deceptive online ads.

Analysts were able to verify that the Bitdefender agent successfully blocked the suspicious process, preventing its execution and mitigating the threat. 

 
